Former Secretary to the Government of the Federation and presidential hopeful, Anyim Pius Anyim, said he met with billionaire businessman, Ned Nwoko, and some Nollywood stars, who promised to support his presidential ambition, in the forthcoming 2023 general election. According to him, he was perceived as a diligent, trustworthy and visionary candidate, who could lead Nigeria into the future. Anyim made this known in a post on his official Facebook page. “Yesterday, I met with Hon. Ned Nwoko, Chairman Actors Guild of Nigeria; Mr Emeka Rollas, President, Actors Guild of Nigeria; Barr. Kenneth Okonkwo, veteran Nollywood actor, and other notable Nollywood actors, to discuss how Nigeria could be better. “They all reiterated their commitment to supporting me in my quest as they saw me as a diligent, trustworthy and visionary candidate who could lead Nigeria into the future,” the post read. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com